criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Pregnant women who:

          1. are ≥ 18 years;

          2. are between 13-25 gestational weeks;

          3. have no prior breastfeeding experience or other living biological children;

          4. have a personal cell phone with internet access and an unlimited text message plan;
             and

          5. intend to exclusively, or nearly exclusively breastfeed (<2 ounces of artificial milk
             per day) for at least 2 months postpartum; (6) plan to deliver their infant at MWH.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Maternal, fetal, or neonatal conditions or complications with the potential to
             physiologically compromise breastfeeding or milk supply (e.g., history of breast
             reduction surgery, infant cardiac defects, postpartum infant ventilator dependence);

          2. current gestation of ≥ 1 fetus;

          3. contraindications to breastfeeding as specified by the American Academy of Pediatrics
             (e.g., HIV+ status).
